After an awareness walk in Nairobi on Wednesday morning to mark World Cerebral Palsy Day, a partnership dinner was hosted at the National Museums of Kenya on Friday evening. The event seeks to raise awareness on cerebral palsy and mobilise resources to expand the cerebral palsy unit at Dr Ribeiro which currently houses over 100 children. In attendance at the dinner were Special Porgrammes PS Josephta Oyiela Mukobe, BSD Group director Eva Muraya, Dr Ribeiro principal Rose Mureu and Orion Foundation founder Mary Warigia.